Warawara (Aymara warawara star, also spelled Wara Wara) is a  lake in Bolivia. It is situated in the Oruro Department, Sebasti√°n Pagador Province, which is identical to the Santiago de Huari Municipality. The river Jach'uyu (Aymara for "big corral", Jachuyo) originates at the lake. It flows to the north-east.
